16/01/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The country's permanent representative at the Council of Europe, Neven Madey, gave officials in Strasbourg ratification documents for two European conventions Wednesday (15 January).
The Croatian Foreign Ministry says one was on the suppression of terrorism and the other was on environmental protections.
Also Wednesday, Croatia's permanent representative to the UN, Ivan Simonovic, handed over his duties as chairman of the UN Economic and Social Council to the next rotating presidency, Guatemala.
(HINA, HRT - 15/01/03)
